@megamissnortheast || Exploring India’s North East Paradise Unexplored with Mega Miss North East Finalist Undana Leimapokpam from Manipur

Supported by - 
Ministry Of Tourism, Government Of India, North East.

“Kaina Temple located 29 km east of Imphal along the Imphal-Yairipok road, is a serene heaven in Manipur. This verdant hillock holds deep spiritual significance, as it is believed that King Bhagya Chandra received a divine vision here, instructing him to carve Lord Govinda’s statue from a sacred jackfruit tree. ￼

Beyond its sacred history, Kaina captivates visitors with the enchanting Ras Leela dance, a graceful blend of culture and devotion to Lord Krishna. The tranquil surroundings and lush greenery make it an ideal retreat for those seeking spiritual solace and natural beauty.

Experience Kaina Hill—a sanctuary where spirituality and breathtaking landscapes converge to create an unforgettable journey.”
